  "text": "The C-terminal domain (or hemopexin-like domain) is structurally similar to proteins of the hemopexin family. The domain has a relatively large surface area for protein-protein interactions e.g. cell membrane receptors. It is ellipsoidshaped with propeller-like subdomain, where each leaf of the \"propeller\" is composed of 4 antiparallel -sheets and onehelix. The first and fourth leaf are linked by a disulfide bridge [CITATION_1] . As published for collagenase-1, the catalytic and ",
